North Escobares first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusTX/> Prior to the 2010 census, part of North Escobares CDP was incorporated into [[Escobares, Texas|Escobares]] city and parts were taken to form new CDPs ([[Escobar I, Texas|Escobar I]], [[JF Villarreal, Texas|JF Villarreal CDP]], [[Loma Vista, Texas|Loma Vista CDP]], [[Moraida, Texas|Moraida CDP]], [[Pena, Texas|Pena CDP]], and [[Rivera, Texas|Rivera CDP]]) and additional area was lost.<ref name=2010CensusTX/>

